fields.title: Blink
fields.description: The fabled dagger used by the fastest assassin ever to walk the lands.

fields.title: Overwhelming blink
fields.description: A horrifying dagger forged in the chaos maw and nigh untouchable by mortal hands.

fields.title: Swift blink
fields.description: A cunning blade able to anticipate and enable its bearer's movements.

fields.title: Arcane blink
fields.description: A revitalizing tool to help bear the weight of arcane expenditure.

fields.title: Blades of attack
fields.description: The damage of these small, concealable blades should not be underestimated.

fields.title: Broadsword
fields.description: The classic weapon of choice for knights, this blade is sturdy and reliable for slaying enemies.

fields.title: Chainmail
fields.description: A medium weave of metal chains.

fields.title: Claymore
fields.description: A sword that can cut through armor, it's a commonly chosen first weapon for budding swordsmen.

fields.title: Helm of iron will
fields.description: The helmet of a legendary warrior who fell in battle.

fields.title: Javelin
fields.description: A rather typical spear that can sometimes pierce through an enemy's armor when used to attack.

fields.title: Mithril hammer
fields.description: A hammer forged of pure mithril.

fields.title: Platemail
fields.description: Thick metal plates that protect the entire upper body. Avoid dropping on feet.

fields.title: Quarterstaff
fields.description: A basic staff that allows you to strike quickly.

fields.title: Quelling blade
fields.description: The axe of a fallen gnome, it allows you to effectively maneuver the forest.

fields.title: Faerie fire
fields.description: The ethereal flames from the ever-burning ruins of Kindertree ignite across realities.

fields.title: Infused raindrop
fields.description: Elemental protection from magical assaults.

fields.title: Wind lace
fields.description: Hasten to battle on wind-touched heels.

fields.title: Ring of protection
fields.description: A glimmering ring that defends its bearer.

fields.title: Stout shield
fields.description: One man's wine barrel bottom is another man's shield.

fields.title: Moon shard
fields.description: Said to be a tear from the lunar goddess Selemene.

fields.title: Gauntlets
fields.description: Studded leather gloves that add brute strength.

fields.title: Slippers
fields.description: Light boots made from spider skin that tingles your senses.

fields.title: Mantle
fields.description: A beautiful sapphire mantle worn by generations of queens.

fields.title: Branches
fields.description: A seemingly ordinary branch, its ironlike qualities are bestowed upon the bearer.

fields.title: Belt of strength
fields.description: A valued accessory for improving vitality.

fields.title: Boots of elves
fields.description: A tensile fabric often used for its light weight and ease of movement.

fields.title: Robe
fields.description: This robe corrupts the soul of the user, but provides wisdom in return.

fields.title: Circlet
fields.description: An elegant circlet designed for human princesses.

fields.title: Crown
fields.description: A stately crown created to ensure a well-meaning but ungifted heir could fend off usurpers and govern with a strong hand.

fields.title: Ogre axe
fields.description: You grow stronger just by holding it.

fields.title: Blade of alacrity
fields.description: A long blade imbued with time magic.

fields.title: Staff of wizardry
fields.description: A staff of magical powers passed down from the eldest mages.

fields.title: Ultimate orb
fields.description: A mystical orb containing the essence of life.

fields.title: Gloves
fields.description: A pair of magical gloves that seems to render weapons weightless.

fields.title: Blitz knuckles
fields.description: An underground arcanist's update of a back-alley classic.

fields.title: Lifesteal
fields.description: A mask that drains the energy of those caught in its gaze.

fields.title: Voodoo mask
fields.description: A mask tuned to sip the arcane bindings that pass between caster and foe.

fields.title: Ring of regen
fields.description: This ring is considered a good luck charm among the Gnomes.

fields.title: Ring of tarrasque
fields.description: An ageless ring forged with an otherwise simple blood magic amplified by the presumed source of its key component.

fields.title: Sobi mask
fields.description: A mask commonly used by mages and warlocks for various rituals.

fields.title: Boots
fields.description: Fleet footwear, increasing movement.

fields.title: Gem
fields.description:
Not one thrall creature of the depths,
Nor spirit bound in drowning's keep,
Nor Maelrawn the Tentacular,
Shall rest till seas, gem comes to sleep.

fields.title: Cloak
fields.description: A cloak made of a magical material that works to dispel any magic cast on it.

fields.title: Talisman of evasion
fields.description: A necklace that allows you to anticipate enemy attacks.

fields.title: Cheese
fields.description: Made from the milk of a long lost Furbolg vendor, it restores the vitality of those who taste it.

fields.title: Magic stick
fields.description: A simple wand used to channel magic energies, it is favored by apprentice wizards and great warlocks alike.

fields.title: Magic wand
fields.description: A simple wand used to channel magic energies, it is favored by apprentice wizards and great warlocks alike.

fields.title: Ghost
fields.description: Imbues the wielder with a ghostly presence, allowing them to evade physical damage.

fields.title: Clarity
fields.description: Clear water that enhances the ability to meditate.

fields.title: Enchanted mango
fields.description: The bittersweet flavors of Jidi Isle are irresistible to amphibians.

fields.title: Flask
fields.description: A magical salve that can quickly mend even the deepest of wounds.

fields.title: Dust
fields.description: One may hide visage, but never volume.

fields.title: Bottle
fields.description: An old bottle that survived the ages, the contents placed inside become enchanted.

fields.title: Ward observer
fields.description: A form of half-sentient plant, often cultivated by apprentice wizards.

fields.title: Ward sentry
fields.description: A form of plant originally grown in the garden of a fearful king.

fields.title: Ward dispenser
fields.description: Advancements in stacking efficiency have made wards easier to carry than ever.

fields.title: Tango
fields.description: Forage to survive on the battlefield.

fields.title: Tango single
fields.description: Om nom nom.

fields.title: Courier
fields.description: Losing the courier is punishable by death.

fields.title: Flying courier
fields.description: The faithful mount upon which soar the fortunes of battle.

fields.title: Tpscroll
fields.description: What a hero truly needs.

fields.title: Travel boots
fields.description: Winged boots that grant omnipresence.

fields.title: Travel boots 2
fields.description: Winged boots that grant omnipresence.

fields.title: Phase boots
fields.description: Boots that allow the wearer to travel between the ether.

fields.title: Demon edge
fields.description: One of the oldest weapons forged by the Demon-Smith Abzidian, it killed its maker when he tested its edge.

fields.title: Eagle
fields.description: Capturing the majestic call of an eagle, this mystical horn brings limitless dexterity to those who hear it.

fields.title: Reaver
fields.description: A massive axe capable of tearing whole mountains down.

fields.title: Relic
fields.description: An ancient weapon that often turns the tides of war.

fields.title: Hyperstone
fields.description: A mystical, carved stone that boosts the fervor of the holder.

fields.title: Ring of health
fields.description: A shiny ring found beneath a fat halfling's corpse.

fields.title: Void stone
fields.description: Jewelry that was once used to channel nether realm magic, this ring pulses with energy.

fields.title: Mystic staff
fields.description: Enigmatic staff made of only the most expensive crystals.

fields.title: Energy booster
fields.description: This lapis gemstone is commonly added to the collection of wizards seeking to improve their presence in combat.

fields.title: Point booster
fields.description: A perfectly formed amethyst that nourishes body and mind when held.

fields.title: Vitality booster
fields.description: A ruby gemstone that has been passed down through generations of warrior kin.

fields.title: Fluffy hat
fields.description: Fine and functional foppery for the fashion-forward fighter.

fields.title: Power treads
fields.description: A pair of tough-skinned boots that change to meet the demands of the wearer.

fields.title: Hand of midas
fields.description: Preserved through unknown magical means, the Hand of Midas is a weapon of greed, sacrificing animals to line the owner's pockets.

fields.title: Oblivion staff
fields.description: Deceptively hidden as an ordinary staff, it is actually very powerful, much like the Eldritch who originally possessed it.

fields.title: Witch blade
fields.description: A spiteful blade inadvertently possessed by the soul of its incautious creator.

fields.title: Pers
fields.description: A gem that grants heart to the bearer.

fields.title: Poor mans shield
fields.description: A busted old shield that seems to block more than it should.

fields.title: Bracer
fields.description: The bracer is a common choice to toughen up defenses and increase longevity.

fields.title: Wraith band
fields.description: A circlet with faint whispers echoing about it.

fields.title: Null talisman
fields.description: A small gemstone attached to several chains.

fields.title: Mekansm
fields.description: A glowing jewel formed out of assorted parts that somehow fit together perfectly.

fields.title: Vladmir
fields.description: An eerie mask that is haunted with the malice of a fallen vampire.

fields.title: Wraith pact
fields.description: A sentient amulet whose animus shakes the courage of even the strongest foes.

fields.title: Buckler
fields.description: A powerful shield that imbues the bearer with the strength of heroes past, it is capable of protecting entire armies in battle.

fields.title: Ring of basilius
fields.description: Ring given as a reward to the greatest mages.

fields.title: Holy locket
fields.description: A prized relic long thought lost forever in a failed crusade.

fields.title: Pipe
fields.description: A powerful artifact of mysterious origin, it creates barriers against magical forces.

fields.title: Urn of shadows
fields.description: Contains the ashes of powerful demons.

fields.title: Headdress
fields.description: Creates a soothing aura that restores allies in battle.

fields.title: Sheepstick
fields.description: The most guarded relic among the cult of Vyse, it is the most coveted weapon among magi.

fields.title: Orchid
fields.description: A garnet rod constructed from the essence of a fire demon.

fields.title: Bloodthorn
fields.description: A reviled blade that bites deeper with each wriggle of its victim's final throes.

fields.title: Echo sabre
fields.description: A deceptively swift blade imbued with resonant magic.

fields.title: Cyclone
fields.description: A mysterious scepter passed down through the ages, its disruptive winds can be used for good or evil.

fields.title: Wind waker
fields.description: Proof enough to some that unseen forces manipulate the happenings of the material plane.

fields.title: Aether lens
fields.description: Polished with the incantation of his final breath, the gift of a dying mage to his sickly son.

fields.title: Force staff
fields.description: Allows you to manipulate others, for good or evil.

fields.title: Hurricane pike
fields.description: A legendary pike once held as royal sigil of the ancient wyvern riders.

fields.title: Dagon
fields.description: A lesser wand that grows in power the longer it is used, it brings magic to the fingertips of the user.

fields.title: Dagon 2
fields.description: A lesser wand that grows in power the longer it is used, it brings magic to the fingertips of the user.

fields.title: Dagon 3
fields.description: A lesser wand that grows in power the longer it is used, it brings magic to the fingertips of the user.

fields.title: Dagon 4
fields.description: A lesser wand that grows in power the longer it is used, it brings magic to the fingertips of the user.

fields.title: Dagon 5
fields.description: A lesser wand that grows in power the longer it is used, it brings magic to the fingertips of the user.

fields.title: Necronomicon
fields.description: Considered the ultimate in necromancy and demonology, a powerful malefic force is locked within its pages.

fields.title: Necronomicon 2
fields.description: Considered the ultimate in necromancy and demonology, a powerful malefic force is locked within its pages.

fields.title: Necronomicon 3
fields.description: Considered the ultimate in necromancy and demonology, a powerful malefic force is locked within its pages.

fields.title: Ultimate scepter
fields.description: The scepter of a wizard with demigod-like powers.

fields.title: Ultimate scepter 2
fields.description: The scepter of a wizard with demigod-like powers.

fields.title: Ultimate scepter roshan
fields.description: The scepter of a wizard with demigod-like powers.

fields.title: Aghanims shard
fields.description: With origins known only to a single wizard, fragments of this impossible crystal are nearly as coveted as the renowned scepter itself.

fields.title: Refresher
fields.description: A powerful artifact created for wizards.

fields.title: Assault
fields.description: Forged in the depths of the nether reaches, this hellish mail provides an army with increased armor and attack speed.

fields.title: Heart
fields.description: Preserved heart of an extinct monster, it bolsters the bearer's fortitude.

fields.title: Black king bar
fields.description: A powerful staff imbued with the strength of giants.

fields.title: Aegis
fields.description: The Immortal was said to own a shield that protected him from death itself.

fields.title: Shivas guard
fields.description: Said to have belonged to a goddess, today it retains much of its former power.

fields.title: Bloodstone
fields.description: The Bloodstone's bright ruby color is unmistakable on the battlefield, as the owner seems to have infinite vitality and spirit.

fields.title: Sphere
fields.description: This magical sphere once protected one of the most famous heroes in history.

fields.title: Lotus orb
fields.description: The jewel at its center still reflects a pale image of its creator.

fields.title: Vanguard
fields.description: A powerful shield that defends its wielder from even the most vicious of attacks.

fields.title: Crimson guard
fields.description: A cuirass originally built to protect against the dreaded Year Beast.

fields.title: Blade mail
fields.description: A razor-sharp coat of mail, it is the choice of selfless martyrs in combat.

fields.title: Soul booster
fields.description: Regain lost courage.

fields.title: Hood of defiance
fields.description: A furred, magic resistant headpiece that is feared by wizards.

fields.title: Eternal shroud
fields.description: A pristine hood that feeds upon strife to empower its owner.

fields.title: Rapier
fields.description: So powerful, it cannot have a single owner.

fields.title: Monkey king bar
fields.description: A powerful staff used by a master warrior.

fields.title: Radiance
fields.description: A divine weapon that causes damage and a bright burning effect that lays waste to nearby enemies.

fields.title: Butterfly
fields.description: Only the mightiest and most experienced of warriors can wield the Butterfly, but it provides incredible dexterity in combat.

fields.title: Greater crit
fields.description: A weapon of incredible power that is difficult for even the strongest of warriors to control.

fields.title: Basher
fields.description: A feared weapon in the right hands, this maul's ability to shatter the defenses of its opponents should not be underestimated.

fields.title: Bfury
fields.description: The bearer of this mighty axe gains the ability to cut down swaths of enemies at once.

fields.title: Manta
fields.description: An axe made of reflective materials that causes confusion amongst enemy ranks.

fields.title: Lesser crit
fields.description: A blade forged from rare crystals, it seeks weak points in enemy armor.

fields.title: Dragon lance
fields.description: The forward charge of the wyvern host grants no quarter.

fields.title: Armlet
fields.description: Weapon of choice among brutes, the bearer sacrifices his life energy to gain immense strength and power.

fields.title: Invis sword
fields.description: The blade of a fallen king, it allows you to move unseen and strike from the shadows.

fields.title: Silver edge
fields.description: Once used to slay an unjust king, only to have the kingdom erupt into civil war in the aftermath.

fields.title: Sange and yasha
fields.description: Sange and Yasha, when attuned by the moonlight and used together, become a very powerful combination.

fields.title: Kaya and sange
fields.description: Two of three known items of unimaginable power that many believe were crafted at the same enchanter's forge.

fields.title: Yasha and kaya
fields.description: Yasha and Kaya when paired together share a natural resonance.

fields.title: Satanic
fields.description: Immense power at the cost of your soul.

fields.title: Mjollnir
fields.description: Thor's magical hammer, made for him by the dwarves Brok and Eitri.

fields.title: Skadi
fields.description: Extremely rare artifact, guarded by the azure dragons.

fields.title: Sange
fields.description: Sange is an unusually accurate weapon, seeking weak points automatically.

fields.title: Helm of the dominator
fields.description: The powerful headpiece of a dead necromancer.

fields.title: Helm of the overlord
fields.description: The powerful headpiece of a dead necromancer.

fields.title: Maelstrom
fields.description: A hammer forged for the gods themselves, Maelstrom allows its user to harness the power of lightning.

fields.title: Gungir
fields.description: Bindings forged by impossible means to leash an ancient evil.

fields.title: Desolator
fields.description: A wicked weapon, used in torturing political criminals.

fields.title: Yasha
fields.description: Yasha is regarded as the swiftest weapon ever created.

fields.title: Mask of madness
fields.description: Once this mask is worn, its bearer becomes an uncontrollable aggressive force.

fields.title: Diffusal blade
fields.description: An enchanted blade that allows the user to cut straight into the enemy's soul.

fields.title: Ethereal blade
fields.description: A flickering blade of a ghastly nature, it is capable of dealing damage in both magical and physical planes.

fields.title: Soul ring
fields.description: A ring that feeds on the souls of those who wear it.

fields.title: Arcane boots
fields.description: Magi equipped with these boots are valued in battle.

fields.title: Octarine core
fields.description: At the core of spellcraft are spectrums only the very gifted can sense.

fields.title: Orb of venom
fields.description: Envenoms your veapon with the venom of a venomous viper.

fields.title: Blight stone
fields.description: An unnerving stone unearthed beneath the Fields of Endless Carnage.

fields.title: Orb of corrosion
fields.description: Seepage from the wounds of a warrior deity, sealed in an arcanist's orb following a campaign of vicious slaughter.

fields.title: Falcon blade
fields.description: An enchanted blade that long ago raised a hopeless urchin from pauper to king.

fields.title: Mage slayer
fields.description: Forged by a secret order in The Third Age of Praxa'cia to fell the False King.

fields.title: Ancient janggo
fields.description: A relic that enchants the bodies of those around it for swifter movement in times of crisis.

fields.title: Boots of bearing
fields.description: Resplendent footwear fashioned for the ancient herald that first dared spread the glory of Stonehall beyond the original borders of its nascent claim.

fields.title: Medallion of courage
fields.description: The bearer has no fear of combat.

fields.title: Solar crest
fields.description: A talisman forged to honor the daytime sky.

fields.title: Smoke of deceit
fields.description: The charlatan wizard Myrddin's only true contribution to the arcane arts.

fields.title: Tome of knowledge
fields.description: That which raises beast to man and man to god.

fields.title: Veil of discord
fields.description: The headwear of corrupt magi.

fields.title: Revenants brooch
fields.description: The cursed brooch of a fallen guardian who stalks forever between the veil of life and death.

fields.title: Guardian greaves
fields.description: One of many holy instruments constructed to honor the Omniscience.

fields.title: Rod of atos
fields.description: Atos, the Lord of Blight, has his essence stored in this deceptively simple wand.

fields.title: Iron talon
fields.description: A simple but effective weapon devised to quell a great Hellbear uprising.

fields.title: Abyssal blade
fields.description: The lost blade of the Commander of the Abyss, this edge cuts into an enemy's soul.

fields.title: Heavens halberd
fields.description: This halberd moves with the speed of a smaller weapon, allowing the bearer to win duels that a heavy edge would not.

fields.title: Ring of aquila
fields.description: The ring of the fallen Warlord Aquila continues to support armies in battle.

fields.title: Tranquil boots
fields.description: While they increase the longevity of the wearer, this boot is not particularly reliable.

fields.title: Glimmer cape
fields.description: The stolen cape of a master illusionist.

fields.title: Royal jelly
fields.description: To those who harvest olgru jelly, success serves more than mere profit--it's often the means to survival--for only the jelly itself can cure the ravages that follow a sting from the vigilant denizens of the giant hives.

fields.title: Vambrace
fields.description: The coveted treasure that divided the heirs of Queen Raiya upon her death, resulting in the eventual downfall of her kingdom.

fields.title: Diffusal blade 2
fields.description: An enchanted blade that allows the user to cut straight into the enemy's soul.
